<P><Q REND="inline">'D&mdash;n their Figures, cries the Squire; a pretty ci|vilized Nation truly, where Women are above the Law. And what mu&s;t I &s;tand &s;ending a Parcel of Compliments to a confounded Whore, that keeps away a Daughter from her own natural Father? I tell you, Si&s;ter, I am not &s;o ignorant as you think me.&mdash;I know you would have Women above the Law, but it is all a Lie; I heard his Lord&s;hip &s;ay at 'Size, that no one is above the Law. But this of yours is <HI>Hannover</HI> Law, I &s;uppo&s;e.'</Q></P>
