<P>IT is almo&s;t impo&s;&s;ible for the be&s;t Parent to ob&s;e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> an exact Impartiality to his Children, even thou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters"> no &s;uperior Merit &s;hould bia&s;s his Affection; but &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> a Parent can hardly be blamed, when that Superior determines his Preference.</P>
