<P><HI>Blifil</HI> indeed &s;oon cured his Uncle of all Anger o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> the Score of Deceit, by many Vows and Prote&s;tati+ons that he had been deceived him&s;elf, with which th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> many Declarations of <HI>We&s;tern</HI> very well tallied; bu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> now to per&s;uade <HI>Allworthy</HI> to con&s;ent to the renewing his Addre&s;&s;es, was a Matter of &s;uch apparent Difficul+ty, that the very Appearance was &s;ufficient to hav<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> deterred a le&s;s enterprizing Genius: but this young Gentleman &s;o well knew his own Talents, that no+thing within the Province of Cunning, &s;eemed to him hard to be atchieved.</P>
